17/01/2007
ROME, Italy -- Interior Minister Guliano Amato called on the Western Balkan states Tuesday (January 16th) to act decisively against organised crime and to boost co-operation between their police forces and Europol. Amato was speaking at a conference titled "Western Balkan States' Perspective for Entry in the EU and Italy's Role", held by the government in Rome. He particularly stressed the need for stepped up institutional efforts against crime in Albania and Montenegro. 
In other news Tuesday, Macedonia signed a deal on strategic co-operation with Europol. The accord would lead to more efficient exchanges of strategic and technical information related to fighting organised crime. (Vijesti, Utrinski Vesnik - 17/01/07; Makfax - 16/01/07)
